<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871203-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:PPG Industries Inc.</HL><DD> 12/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PPGTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   PPG Industries Inc. said it formed a joint venture with Caracas, Venezuela-based Sudamtex de Venezuela C.A. that calls for the purchase of fiberglass operations of a Sudamtex subsidiary. Terms weren't disclosed.    The venture is PPG's third this year outside the U.S. involving the manufacture of continuous strand fiberglass, used in the marine, construction and automotive industries.    PPG, a producer of float glass, chemicals, coatings and resins, said the latest venture includes rebuilding Sudamtex's manufacturing furnace at Barcelona, Venezuela, and tripling its capacity. The plant employs 120 people. </TEXT></DOC>